Functional Objectives: 
• Design a user registration and authentication system in which tenants will be able to 
create accounts and log in safely. 
• Add property management functionality that enables tenants to add, edit and delete 
property information such as landlord and agent information. 
• Introduce bond tracking features that would allow tenants to keep track of bond amounts, 
payment dates, reference numbers and change bond status (Paid/Pending/Refunded). 
• Offer management of inspection records where tenants can create an inspection record, 
add condition comments and post photo evidence. 
• Provide document storage capability to enable uploading of lease agreements, bond 
receipts and other tenancy documents. 
• Design a dashboard displaying bond summaries, upcoming inspection dates, and recent 
documents. 
Technical Objectives: 
• Use MD5 hash to encrypt passwords and store them in a secure encoding as required by 
the project. 
• Make sure that data transmission is all encrypted on HTTPS. 
• The system should be optimized to ensure that the pages are loaded in less than 3 seconds 
and the API responses in less than half a second. 
• Implement an operational web application prototype that can be accessed by the use of 
the modern web browsers.
